vstore.framework.file

Class VFileType

  • java.lang.Object
    • vstore.framework.file.VFileType

  • public final class VFileType
extends java.lang.Object
    This class contains constants that denote the supported mime types of the vStore framework.

      • getExtensionFromMimeType

        public static java.lang.String getExtensionFromMimeType(java.lang.String mimetype)
        This method iterates over the map of possible mime types and returns the first extension for which the mime type matches.
        Parameters:
        mimetype - The mime type to get the extension for.
        Returns:
        The file extension corresponding to the given mime type. Will be the default extension "vstor" if the mime type is not supported.

      • getSupportedTypes

        public static java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> getSupportedTypes()
        Get a list of file types that are supported by the vStore framework.
        Returns:
        Returns a HashMap where the keys represent file extensions and the values represent the corresponding MIME type.

      • isMimeTypeSupported

        public static boolean isMimeTypeSupported(java.lang.String mimetype)
        This method checks, if the given mime type is supported by the framework.
        Parameters:
        mimetype - The mimetype to check.
        Returns:
        True, if the file type is supported. False, if not.

      • isExtensionSupported

        public static boolean isExtensionSupported(java.lang.String mimetype)
        This method checks, if the given file extension is supported by the framework.
        Parameters:
        mimetype - The file extension to check.
        Returns:
        True, if the file extension is supported. False, if not.
